message: /* top */ change link target, as ideas of spirits extend far beyond the nineteenth-century movement described in [[Spiritualism]]

Apologies - I explained the removal in a smaller edit before I removed the content. The inclusion of information about Paddington Bear and the Queen under "Modern religion" is clearly comical. None of the sources link it to psychopomps and some of the prose is clearly meant to be humorous ("This spontaneous folk ritual has no official status in the Church of England"). I am removing it for this reason - it is not encyclopedic.
